 ) and   Pawlicki  , Assyrian/Chaldean   Polous   and   Polus  . In France, this surname is most common in Brittany (see 2 below).","Breton (mainly Finistère): from a Frenchified form of the personal name <i>Paol</i>, Breton form of   Paul  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Phóil</b> ‘son of Paul’. Compare   McFall  ."]}]},{"name":"Walter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old French personal name of Germanic (Frankish) origin, derived from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i>, <i>hari</i> ‘army’. This was adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, superseding the native Old English form, <i>Wealdhere</i>. It was a very popular name in medieval England, normally pronounced ‘Water’."],"variants":[{"name":"Walther","meanings":["from <i>wald</i> ‘rule’ + <i>heri</i> ‘army’; name of the famous medieval minnesinger  Walther von der Vogelweide  (  <i>c.</i>1170– <i>c.</i>1230 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Walter Pollard was born in 1223, in Europe. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth de La Waye. He died in 1286, at the age of 63."},"et":{"1223–1286":"1223–1286","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1286":"1286","1240":"1240","Ermington, Devon, England":"Ermington, Devon, England","Europe":"Europe"},"fi":{"1223–1286":"1223–1286","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1286":"1286","1240":"1240","Ermington, Devon, England":"Ermington, Devon, England","Europe":"Europe"},"fr":{"1223–1286":"1223–1286","1225–Female":"1225–Décédée","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","1225":"1225","1223":"1223","1286":"1286","1240":"1240","Ermington, Devon, England":"Ermington, Devon, Angleterre","Europe":"Europe","lifeSummary":"Walter Pollard est né en 1223, à Europe. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Elizabeth de La Waye. Il est décédé en 1286, à l’âge de 63 ans."},"de":{"1223–1286":"1223–1286","1225